                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#128rb">Fol. 128rb</locus>: Donation note. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in red by the same hand that inserted the names of the donor and other persons in erasures. 
Däğğazmač Säba Gadǝs (sic for Subagadis, Säbagadis), called also by his baptismal name Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus, is mentioned as the buyer and donor of the Ms.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Many omissions and/or corrections are written interlineally, sometimes in the main hand, sometimes in a secondary hand: e.g., fols. 7ra, 8vb, 10ra, 21va, 27vb, 28vb, 34rab, 39rab, 40rab, 40vb, 41vb, 62ra, 83va, 86va, 91vb, 110ra, 117ra, 118vab. &#xD;
- Immediate corrections are indicated by series of red dots around the incorrect letter: 25va, 39va, 76vb, 98rb, 126ra.&#xD;
- Occasionally words or parts of a word are crossed out: e.g., fols. 14ra, 43vb, 60va. &#xD;
- A few erasures (immediate corrections?) marked with thin parallel lines: e.g., fols. 28ra, 37rb, 38ra, 52va, 84rb, 89rb, 89vb, 90rb, 103rb; one marked with a simple ornamental band: fol. 41va. &#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign (in the shape of +) indicating the place where the omission, written in the upper margin, belong: fol. 80ra.&#xD;
- Stamp of the church or donor: fols. 5r, 23v, 25v, 48v, 76v, 102v, 109r, 121r, 128r.&#xD;
- The name of the church is written in red felt-tip pen: fol. 1r.&#xD;
- Pen trial: fol. 1r.</item>
                     </list>
